        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:10PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 309 PM CDT, emergency management reported a strong thunderstorm
near Huntsville International Airport, or near Madison, moving
northeast at 25 mph. Pea sized hail was reported with this storm in
Decatur.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Emergency management.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Decatur, Madison, Athens, Hartselle, Redstone Arsenal,
Priceville, Trinity, Owens Cross Roads, and Triana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
